description: {"blocks":[{"key":"4u687","text":"A transmission electron microscope (TEM) enables the magnification and visualisation of cell and tissue ultrastructure that cannot otherwise be resolved using a light microscope. In transmission electron microscopy, a high energy electron beam generated from an electron gun is focused by electromagnetic lenses onto an ultrathin section of plastic embedded specimen. Electrons are transmitted through the specimen onto a fluorescent screen based on sample density, and an image acquired by a digital camera. Here, a protocol for preparing cells for TEM ultrastructural analysis is described. A cell sample is fixed, dehydrated and infiltrated with resin. The resin is then polymerised, and embedded cell sample sectioned using an ultramicrotome. Ultrathin sections are contrasted with heavy metals prior to imaging using a TEM. Options for faster processing using a Microwave processor are described for relevant steps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1apr4","text":"Remove the supernatant and add approximately 100 μl (2 drops) of the pre-warmed 4% aqueous agarose to the cell pellet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bmhd2","text":"Optionally, to obtain a concentrated cell pellet, return the microcentrifuge tube containing cells in 4% aqueous agarose to the Bain Marie or heat block until the agarose liquefies, and then pellet cells using a benchtop microcentrifuge.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fu8su","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"52o39","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"18pu2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"374cg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bsr9d","text":"Solidify the 4% aqueous agarose with cells by cooling at 4 degrees Celsius for 10 minutes.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c6jo2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"82anf","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4babm","text":"Cut off the extreme tip of the microcentrifuge tube (avoiding the cells) using a razor blade and push the sample out of the tube using a wooden stick.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9iuni","text":"Place the agarose embedded cell block on a Teflon plate or dental wax sheet and cut the block in half using a scalpel or double edged razor blade. Cut each block half into strips and then cut each strip into cubes no larger than 1mm3. Carefully place the agarose-embedded cell cubes into a 5ml tube using forceps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":232,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"66ou2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"pja6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1qu88","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bg9a5","text":"For Steps 14-27, do not proceed if samples float following ethanol, acetone or Epon resin infiltration. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":12,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"463s7","text":"Well-infiltrated samples should sink in solution. If they do not, samples may require extended infiltration times. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eugn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"64hvd","text":"Epon resin can be stored in the freezer but must come to room temperature before use. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bio7n","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ehsoj","text":"The following steps can be performed with or without the use of a PELCO BioWave® Pro+ Microwave Processing System. {"blocks":[{"key":"cr7j6","text":"Dehydrate in 50% ethanol in MilliQ water for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"akqt5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8c44c","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ulvp","text":"Dehydrate in 70% ethanol in MilliQ water for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating. The sample can be left at 4 degrees Celsius, overnight if necessary.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bsma","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fjfvd","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"89a2b","text":"Dehydrate in 90% ethanol in MilliQ water for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"41vjn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"csruq","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"71bk7","text":"Dehydrate in 95% ethanol in MilliQ water for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bord4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2v2qq","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2tvi2","text":"Dehydrate in 100% ethanol for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4ai41","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9ibsk","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cufd5","text":"Dehydrate in 100% anhydrous ethanol for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating. Type 3Å molecular sieves can be added to the ethanol stock solution to dehydrate the solvent prior to use. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dpouu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fuf44","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f730g","text":"Dehydrate in 100% acetone for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1dvsa","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dv8uf","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fl22n","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e11a0","text":"Propylene oxide can be used as an alternative to acetone (Steps 21-25), but is extremely toxic and may dehydrate samples too intensively, causing ultrastructural damage. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8o1em","text":"Dehydrate in 100% anhydrous acetone for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating. Type 3Å molecular sieves can be added to the acetone stock solution to dehydrate the solvent prior to use. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"csn06","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"hrva","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b8k7l","text":"Optionally Infiltrate with 100% anhydrous acetone : epon resin (3 : 1 ratio) overnight at room temperature, agitating. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"evfts","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"64avc","text":"Biowave settings: 3 minutes, 250W, Vacuum on.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c922n","text":"Infiltrate with 100% anhydrous acetone : epon resin (1 : 1 ratio) for 6 hours at room temperature, agitating. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8cpem","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cl843","text":"Biowave settings: 3 minutes, 250W, Vacuum on.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2gpq5","text":"Infiltrate with 100% anhydrous acetone : epon resin (1 : 3 ratio) overnight at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5cjuc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4aert","text":"Biowave settings: 3 minutes, 250W, Vacuum on. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dl2ne","text":"Infiltrate with 100% epon resin for 6 hours at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dums7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4vi7q","text":"Biowave settings: 3 minutes, 250W, Vacuum on.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bigbb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2e6ft","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"22okp","text":"Infiltrate with 100% epon resin overnight at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"63cv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"458sq","text":"Biowave settings: 3 minutes, 250W, Vacuum on.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"58iv6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"se21","text":"Residual acetone can adversely impact resin infiltration and polymerisation. A third 100% resin infiltration step may  be required to prevent this.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9bdkf","text":"Transfer samples to labelled plastic embedding moulds, flat bottom BEEM® capsules or standard tip BEEM® capsules containing 100% epon resin. Polymerise in an oven set to 60 degrees Celsius for 24-48 hours. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"435mh","text":"Mount the resin-embedded cell block in an ultramicrotome chuck, and secure the chuck to a stereo microscope fitted with a chuck mount. Manually trim the front face and all four edges of the cell block into a trapezoid shape using a double edge razor blade. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eitp5","text":"Transfer the chuck and resin-embedded cell block to a Leica UC7 ultramicrotome and secure in place. Trim the front surface of the block face until a full face of cells has been obtained. Trim manually using a 0.5 μm feed and a 45 degree glass knife (thickness 6.4 mm or 8 mm) or suitable diamond knife, for example a Diatome 35 degree angle ultra semi diamond knife.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"63i8u","text":"To check the region of interest:  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8030q","text":"Cut 90 nm gold coloured ultrathin sections at 1 mm/sec using a Leica UC7 ultramicrotome and a Diatome 45 degree angle ultra wet diamond knife. Spread the sections using a Max Wax heat pen to prevent wrinkles. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"248bp","text":"Pick up sections on 50-200 mesh copper or palladium-coated copper grids. Place grids section side up on a sheet of filter paper, cover with a glass petri dish and leave to dry for 10 minutes. Store grids in an enclosed grid box until use.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"am44u","text":"Cut 500 nm semi thin sections at a speed of 1 mm/sec using a Leica UC7 ultramicrotome and 45 degree glass knife fitted with a filtered water-filled boat or suitable diamond knife.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5jh0o","text":"Retrieve sections with an eyelash or Dalmatian hair mounted on a wooden stick and float sections in a drop of MilliQ water on a slide before drying on a mini hot plate. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8v582","text":"Stain sections with Toluidine blue solution for 10-20 seconds on a mini hot plate before rinsing with MilliQ water and drying on a mini hot plate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d9ld4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dd71c","text":"Toluidine blue stains nucleic acids and proteins, enhancing structural detail of semi thin cell sections.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cpl22","text":"Observe sections with a wide-field light microscope. If the region of interest has not been obtained, trim deeper and repeat Step 31. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"969s3","text":"Place a sheet of parafilm on a clean flat bench or glass board using a small amount of water underneath to keep the film flat. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"74nhd","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b2u24","text":"For the following steps, use fine forceps or a perfect loop to transfer grids from one drop of solution to another, section side down. Use approximately 100-200 μl drops for MilliQ water, and 50-100 μl for uranyl acetate and lead citrate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3v4kv","text":"Stain sections with 0.6% filtered uranyl acetate in MilliQ water for 3 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7gf6v","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c3p86","text":"Uranyl acetate enhances contrast of sections by interacting with proteins and lipids. The solution must be wrapped in foil and stored in a dark place to prevent precipitation from exposure to UV light. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1335v","text":"Rinse 5 x 1 min in MilliQ water.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8abfa","text":"Stain sections with 0.1-0.4% filtered lead citrate in MilliQ water for 3 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4om0l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"qb68","text":"Four drops of 10M sodium hydroxide should be added to the lead citrate stock solution prior to use to prevent lead citrate precipitating to form water-insoluble lead carbonate by exposure to carbon dioxide. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d1mfv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5b3j7","text":"Lead citrate enhances contrast of sections by interacting with proteins and glycogens, and binding to osmium and uranyl acetate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bu4t","text":"Rinse 5 x 1 min in MilliQ water.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"rf3u","text":"Place grids section side up on a sheet of filter paper, cover with a glass petri dish and dry for 10 minutes. Store grids in a grid storage box.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6uend","text":"Place a grid in a transmission electron microscope grid holder for high resolution imaging using a transmission electron microscope.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f3o1s","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8njvi","text":"Example: JEOL JEM-1400-Plus TEM at 80 keV equipped with a high sensitivity bottom mount CMOS 'Flash' camera.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dl21h","text":"Gently detach adherent cells from the bottom of the well-plate/petri dish using a cell scraper. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5kus2","text":"Transfer cells to a 1.5 ml microcentrifuge tube using a 3 ml or 1000 μl transfer pipette, and pellet cells at 1200 rpm for 2 minutes using a benchtop centrifuge.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
